iefly, this is all you need to do:

Install git:
$ sudo apt-get install -y git meld mono-runtime libmono2.0-cil libmono-system-core4.0-cil libmono-system-windows-forms4.0-cil mono-complete

Install one of many diff/merge tools:
$ sudo apt-get install meld

Install mono runtime and required libs:
$ sudo apt-get install mono-runtime 
$ sudo apt-get install libmono2.0-cil libmono-system-core4.0-cil
$ sudo apt-get install libmono-system-windows-forms4.0-cil

On most newer Linux distributions and versions, that should be it!
If, for any reason, mono refuses to load GitForce.exe, you may want to install complete mono package:
$ sudo apt-get install mono-complete















